                <head>16. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 12, Under Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName>
                    and other U.S. officials discussed economic development in Southeast Asia with a
                    Japanese group headed by Foreign Minister Achiro Fujiyama, then visiting
                    Washington. (Memorandum of conversation dated September 15 by <persName>Louis E.
                        Gleeck</persName>, Jr.; Department of State, Conference Files, Lot 63 D 123,
                    CF 1130)</p>
                <pb facs="0076" n="42" xml:id="pg_42"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> discussed Asian development
                    further with Japanese representatives during the Colombo Plan meeting in Seattle
                    on November 11. (<gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 6 from Seattle,
                    November 13; <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., Central Files, 890.00/11–1358)</p>
                <p>Both documents are included in <ref target="frus1958-60v15-16mSupp1">the
                        microfiche supplement</ref>.</p>
            </div>
